VALUES ('c0cc00e2-773a-45d6-a736-7fb13fcbc30d','Small-town Alabama, 1932. Atticus Finch (played by Gregory Peck) is a lawyer and a widower. He has two young children, Jem and Scout. Atticus Finch is currently defending Tom Robinson, a black man accused of raping a white woman. Meanwhile, Jem and Scout are intrigued by their neighbours, the Radleys, and the mysterious, seldom-seen Boo Radley in particular.                Written by grantss tags: Crime Drama Gregory Peck John Megna Frank Overton ');

