INSERT INTO VIDEO_DESCRIPTION (ID,DESCRIPTION )
VALUES ('85d308a2-92b9-441d-b930-53bbea4089fb','Naive and idealistic Jefferson Smith, leader of the Boy Rangers, is appointed on a lark by the spineless governor of his state. He is reunited with the state''s senior senator--presidential hopeful and childhood hero, Senator Joseph Paine. In Washington, however, Smith discovers many of the shortcomings of the political process as his earnest goal of a national boys'' camp leads to a conflict with the state political boss, Jim Taylor. Taylor first tries to corrupt Smith and then later attempts to destroy Smith through a scandal.                Written by James Yu <jamestyu@ccwf.cc.utexas.edu> tags: Comedy Drama James Stewart Jean Arthur Claude Rains ');

