INSERT INTO VIDEO_DESCRIPTION (ID,DESCRIPTION )
VALUES ('14c558e0-433f-46da-8ce2-4852c13c8bc0','From the heights of notoriety to the depths of depravity, John Forbes Nash, Jr. experienced it all. A mathematical genius, he made an astonishing discovery early in his career and stood on the brink of international acclaim. But the handsome and arrogant Nash soon found himself on a painful and harrowing journey of self-discovery. After many years of struggle, he eventually triumphed over his tragedy, and finally - late in life - received the Nobel Prize.                Written by Universal Pictures and DreamWorks Pictures tags: Biography Drama Russell Crowe Ed Harris Jennifer Connelly ');

