INSERT INTO VIDEO_DESCRIPTION (ID,DESCRIPTION )
VALUES ('c38c792e-502c-4c88-a16f-d170ecf82938','In the mid-1970''s, a homely, friendless Australian girl of 8 picks a name out of a Manhattan phone book and writes to him; she includes a chocolate bar. She''s Mary Dinkle, the only child of an alcoholic mother and a distracted father. He''s Max Horowitz, an overweight man with Asperger''s, living alone in New York. He writes back, with chocolate. Thus begins a 20-year correspondence, interrupted by a stay in an asylum and a few misunderstandings. Mary falls in love with a neighbor, saves money to have a birthmark removed and deals with loss. Max has a friendship with a neighbor, tries to control his weight, and finally gets the dream job. Will the two ever meet face to face?                Written by <jhailey@hotmail.com> tags: Animation Comedy Drama Toni Collette Philip Seymour Hoffman Eric Bana ');

